  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mongolia - Silent Emergencies</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This time bound programme interventions will be done in conjunction with organisational strengthening based on key priorities identified by the NS the findings from the recent Disaster Response Capacity Development (DRCD) and Disaster Response Capacity Evaluation (DRCE) conducted in June 2016. BRC is looking to build-in elements of sustainability into the project by piloting new innovation such as forecast-based-financing developed by IFRC Climate Centre and cash readiness capacity building that will enable MRCS to demonstrate to potential partners inside and outside the Movement the cost effectiveness as well as its contribution to movement learning and development. This will enable BRC to support a needs-based disaster preparedness programme and support MRCS to be the first responder during a disaster.</narrative>
  </description>
